Files:
  - src/chipbench/data/**  (dataset: Verilog Gen / Verilog Debugging problem
    triplets, and the three gen_{python,cxxrtl,systemc}_prompt.txt reference
    model prompt templates, vendored verbatim from the upstream repository's
    "Verilog Gen/", "Verilog Debugging/", and "Ref Model Gen/" directories)
  - src/chipbench/Tool_Box/crosslang_verify/**  (cross-language verification
    toolbox, vendored from the upstream repository's
    "Tool_Box/crosslang_verify/" directory; invoked as a subprocess by
    src/chipbench/scorers.py rather than imported, and excluded from this
    project's own lint/type-check/format tooling for that reason — see the
    exclusion comments in pyproject.toml. Three files are modified from
    upstream, all documented in README.md's Evaluation Report and at
    the change itself:
      - src/run_verification.py's link step now also builds and links
        verilated_threads.o, required by Verilator 5.x but not by the
        older Verilator version the upstream script was written against.
      - src/generate_testbench.py's warmup-code generation now gates
        sequential-only DUT initialization behind is_sequential, which the
        upstream version omitted, causing combinational-circuit testbenches
        to reference a clock signal that correctly doesn't exist for them.
      - tools/extract_ports.py's port-extraction regex now (a) only scans
        the first module in a file rather than the whole file, since a
        submodule staged into the same ref.sv for chipbench_refmodel (see
        Bug 2) could otherwise have its ports merged into the top module's,
        and (b) resolves parametrized bit-widths (e.g. [DATA_WIDTH-1:0] or
        [`WORD_SIZE-1:0]) by looking up parameter/localparam/`define values
        in the file, rather than assuming widths are always literal
        integers — the original regex would silently mis-extract the type
        keyword itself ("reg"/"wire"/"logic") as the port name when it hit
        a non-literal width, which is Bug 6 in the known-issues doc.
  - src/chipbench/data/refmodel_prompts/gen_cxxrtl_prompt_fixed.txt  (new
    file, not vendored: a corrected variant of the upstream
    gen_cxxrtl_prompt.txt, rewriting its CXXRTL virtual-method
    instructions/examples to match Yosys v0.60's actual API rather than the
    outdated one upstream's original teaches; used for A/B-testing via
    chipbench_refmodel's cxxrtl_prompt_variant parameter, not the default)
  - src/chipbench/chipbench.py  (adapted: task structure and parameters)
  - src/chipbench/dataset.py  (adapted: dataset loading logic)
  - src/chipbench/scorers.py  (adapted: scoring logic, calling the vendored
    crosslang_verify tool and re-implementing the upstream test.sv
    Mismatches-parsing convention for Icarus Verilog based scoring)
  - src/chipbench/prompts.py  (adapted: reference-model prompt loading)
